{"id": "duc04-testb-49:14#44", "contents": "Albright criticized the growing trend in Russia to shift from a partnership with the West to a more assertive and oppositional stance. She argued that Russia cannot stand alone in the world and that the United States' ability to assist Russia will be hindered if this trend continues. Albright urged patience with the democratic process in Russia and cautioned against assuming the worst, while also emphasizing the need for NATO to be prepared to act in response to the crisis in Kosovo, despite potential Russian opposition."}
